\ examples/132-eics-application.6th
\ Cycle 13C/D — EICS (Krasnovsky 2025, arXiv 2509.07149) applied
\ to Sixth substrate. First substrate-distinguishing positive
\ measurement in catalogue.
\
\ Pre-registered: PREDICTIONS-132.md (sha fda5bf34… attested).
\ Method doc: docs/EICS-HOOK.md.
\ Implementation: scripts/eics_sixth.py.
\
\ === REGIME R FIRES — FIRST POSITIVE SUBSTRATE-DISTINGUISHING SIGNAL ===
\
\ R_overall = 1.7954 (mean EICS_substrate / EICS_random_baseline
\ across 10 canonical Sixth substrates).
\
\ Per substrate R values:
\   cycle_n10_all-self-loops:    7.36   (huge signal)
\   path_n10_self-loops:         2.20
\   ER_n10_p20_all-self-loops:   1.74
\   bipartite_K33_self-loops:    1.40
\   ER_n20_p10_observer-loop:    1.14
\   ER_n20_p20_all-self-loops:   1.12
\   complete_K5:                  1.08
\   ER_n10_p30_observer-loop:    1.03
\   star_n10:                     0.88
\   ER_n10_p10_observer-loop:    0.00   (degenerate at small sparse)
\
\ Strongest signals: structured-topology substrates with all-
\ self-loops (cycle, path).  ER substrates without all-self-loops
\ near 1.0 (no signal).
\
\ Implementation adaptation: macro-Jacobian = A^T (T=10) since
\ single-step Δ_EI < 0 always due to log-det concavity.  T=10
\ accumulates emergence from substrate's iterated NSUM dynamics.
\
\ HONESTY:
\ This finding is REAL per pre-registration:
\   - PREDICTIONS-132 committed BEFORE script
\   - Script committed BEFORE measurement
\   - Regime threshold 1.5 pre-set
\   - R = 1.79 > 1.5 → REGIME R fires
\
\ But interpretation:
\   - EICS captures SPECTRAL structure differences
\   - Cycle/path graphs have distinct eigenstructure vs ER
\   - This is well-known spectral graph theory applied to
\     substrate; not novel substrate-physics
\   - Substrate-distinguishing in the methodological sense
\     (substrate's specific topology produces specific EICS)
\   - Whether this is "substrate-derived" or "spectral-graph-
\     theory-derived" is a fair question for cycle 14
\
\ Honest framing for catalogue:
\   First measurement where Sixth substrate is pre-registered-
\   distinguished from random baseline by a published external
\   metric (EICS).  Modest claim; real result.

use prelude
use debug

